---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---
<MainLayout
  title="About FussyBean"
  description="How FussyBean researches home coffee gear: published specs, aggregated verified-buyer reviews, independent testing, and use-case fit."
>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc-header">
      <span class="doc-kicker">About</span>
      <h1>About FussyBean</h1>
      <p class="doc-lede">
        FussyBean is an independent site that compares home coffee gear by spec
        and use case, so the counter you build is the one you'll actually love.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>
      We cover the hardware: espresso machines, burr grinders, gooseneck kettles,
      scales, and manual brewers, plus the gift-y extras. We rank the machine, not
      the roast. Every piece starts from one question: who is this actually the
      right fit for?
    </p>

    <h2>How we research</h2>
    <p>
      Our recommendations are research-based. We synthesize three kinds of
      evidence into use-case-fit picks:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Published specifications.</strong> Manufacturer spec sheets,
        boiler types, PID details, listed dimensions, and rated figures, read
        carefully and compared across brands.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aggregated verified-buyer reviews.</strong> Patterns across owner
        reviews on Amazon and enthusiast forums, including the critical ones, cited
        to their source.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Independent testing.</strong> Third-party teardowns and measured
        results from outlets like James Hoffmann and Whole Latte Love, cited where
        we lean on them.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We do not claim personal hands-on testing in our content. We are explicit
      about that. If you want a first-person review, look for a reviewer who claims
      one. What we offer instead is careful comparison: spec analysis, aggregated
      owner reports, and honest use-case fit. You can read exactly how we weigh a
      product on our <a href="/how-we-evaluate/">how we evaluate</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      We earn affiliate commissions when you buy through our links. It does not
      change the price you pay, and it does not change which product we recommend.
      We do not accept payment in exchange for positive coverage. Full details are
      in our <a href="/disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Specs change and listings drift. If something is out of date or wrong, tell
      us on the <a href="/contact/">contact</a> page and we will fix it.
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .doc { max-width: var(--content-wide); margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6) var(--space-20); }
  .doc-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .doc-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .doc-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .doc h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc p { line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .doc ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: var(--space-5) 0; }
  .doc li {
    padding: 16px 22px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brass);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .doc li strong { color: var(--color-forest); }
</style>
